olive oil
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet pork mince
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet Peri Peri Sauce
2 radish
½ lemon
1 packet Corn Chips
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 packet garlic aioli
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 coriander
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Drain the sweetcorn
• Heat a frying pan over high heat with
olive oil
• Cook pork mince, spice blend,
garlic paste and corn, tossing, until
browned, 3-5 mins
• Remove pan from heat, then stir
through peri peri sauce

• Thinly slice radish. Cut lemon into
wedges
• Crush corn chips
• In a bowl, combine slaw and aioli

• Microwave tortillas on a plate in
10 second bursts, until warmed
through
• Fill tortillas with slaw, pork and
radish
• Top with cheese, torn coriander and
crushed corn chips
• Squeeze over lemon to serve